<% content_for :title, page_title("Terms") %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Terms of use for Baltimore.ai." %>

<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", crumbs: [ [ "Home", root_path ], [ "Terms", nil ] ] %>

<article class="max-w-2xl">
  <header class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-8 mb-8">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-red-700 font-semibold mb-3">Terms</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight">Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-stone-500 text-sm">Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %Y") %></p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose-editorial">
    <h2>Using the site</h2>
    <p>
      Baltimore.ai is a free directory. You can read it, share it, link to it, and quote from it with attribution. You can't scrape it for commercial purposes without permission.
    </p>

    <h2>Listing accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      We do our best to keep listings accurate but we don't guarantee anything. Companies change. Listings get out of date. If you spot a problem, <a href="<%= contact_path %>">tell us</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Claiming a listing</h2>
    <p>
      By claiming a listing, you confirm you're authorized to represent the company you're claiming. You're responsible for the accuracy of edits you make. You can stop claiming a listing at any time by contacting us.
    </p>

    <h2>Featured and Sponsored content</h2>
    <p>
      Some placements on Baltimore.ai are paid &mdash; clearly labeled "Featured" or "Sponsored." See <a href="<%= editorial_standards_path %>">Editorial Standards</a> for what those labels mean. Editorial coverage and paid placements are kept separate.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      Baltimore.ai is provided as-is. We make no warranties about the accuracy, completeness, or fitness for any particular purpose. We're not liable for decisions you make based on what you read here.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms. Material changes will be highlighted at the top of the page for at least 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      Maryland.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="<%= contact_path %>">contact form</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</article>
